    "body" : "<p>This creates dictionary of text (string):</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Map&lt;String, String&gt; dictionary = new HashMap&lt;String, String&gt;();\n</code></pre>\n<p>you then use it as a:</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>dictionary.put(&quot;key&quot;, &quot;value&quot;);\nString value = dictionary.get(&quot;key&quot;);\n</code></pre>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Works but gives an error you need to keep the constructor class same as the declaration class. I know it inherits from the parent class but, unfortunately it gives an error on runtime.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<pre class=\"lang-java prettyprint-override\"><code>Map&lt;String, String&gt; dictionary = new Map&lt;String, String&gt;();\n</code></pre>\n<p>This works properly.</p>\n"
